 SysOp's Menu contains some MAXs SysOp only functions in one door.

 This is a small update from Version 1.0 of SysOp's Menu ('96).

@endnode
@node run " SysOp's Menu v1.2 by Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS"
@{"°°" link grems}
  _____         _        _ _
 |_   _|_ _  __| |_ __ _| | |
  |   || ' \(_-<  _/ _` | | |
 |_____|_||_/__/\__\__,_|_|_|                        @{b}(c) GREMLiNS MAXsWARE@{ub}

 Firstly (if you already haven't) create a new directory called "gremlins"
 in your doors directory. Assign "gremlins" to your doors path in the user
 startup sequence, eg: "assign gremlins: doors:gremlins" assuming you have
 the doors path assigned also.

 Move the "SM" directory  into the "gremlins" dir & run the door via a BBS
 menu, using MAXs Function 34, eg: "gremlins:sm/sm".

 Need some help, have probs or want to send a msg then @{"contact" link call} me.

@endnode
